The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
Archives
 Business Briefs
 New Delhi, Oct. 10: The RBI board is  meeting in Ranchi tomorrow to review monetary developments  and discuss steps that may be initiated during the mid-term  review of the credit policy on October 30. The RBI is firming  up measures to deal with conflicting problems such as sluggish  demand and slow growth of credit on one hand and rising  liquidity fuelled mainly by foreign exchange inflows on  the other. Mumbai, Oct. 10: The RBI today directed  non-banking finance institutions (NBFCs) to invariably  furnish a copy of loan agreement to borrowers at the time  of sanction of loans. Mumbai, Oct. 10: To protect investors,  Sebi has proposed that investment advisers can engage in  their activities only if it gives them certificates on the  recommendations of the self-regulatory organisations. New Delhi, Oct. 10: Morgan Stanley has  received a merchant banking licence from Sebi. The licence  will enable Morgan Stanley India Company Pvt Ltd to offer  on-shore investment banking advisory and underwriting services. New Delhi, Oct. 10: Petrol and diesel  prices are unlikely to be raised to offset the Rs 185-crore-per-day  loss that public sector oil firms are suffering because  of a surge in international oil prices.
